*Functions in java*
A function is a collection of statments/block of code
used to perform task.
"It is used to reuse the code without retyping the code."
//**Method declaration**\\
"It provids info on methods attributes like
*method name, return type,viibility, parameters and 
body"
//**SYNTAX**\\
public int max(int x, int y) {
    //Mehtod body
}
Here,
*PUBLIC: modifier.
*INT: int is the "return type method"I.E returns int value.
*MAX: name of the method
*intx, int y: list of parameters.

